    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cleaning instruments consisting of a pole or stick attached with a thick bundle of loose strings, yarn, or other absorbent material; used to soak up liquid in cleaning floors and other surfaces.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在一根桿子或棒子上，裝一大捆鬆散的帶子、紗線或其他吸水性材料所組成的清潔器具；清潔地板和其他表面時，用來吸收液體。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Reinigingsgereedschap bestaande uit een paal of stok met daaraan een dikke bundel losse koorden, garen of ander absorberend materiaal; gebruikt om vloeistof op te nemen bij het schoonmaken van vloeren en andere oppervlakken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
